msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/date"
msgid "December 16th, 1944 · Hill 400, Hürtgen Forest, Germany "
msgstr "16 de diciembre de 1944 - Colina 400, Bosque de Hürtgen, Alemania "

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/hold400"
msgid "Hold the hill!"
msgstr "¡Defiendan la colina!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/killmortars"
msgid "Destroy the mortars!"
msgstr "¡Destruyan los morteros!"

#, boost-format
msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/marker_progress"
msgid "%1% out of 5\tareas marked for precise artillery bombardment."
msgstr "%1% de 5 áreas marcadas para un bombardeo preciso de artillería."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/name"
msgid "Hill 400 "
msgstr "Colina 400 "

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/name_big"
msgid "Hill 400"
msgstr "Colina 400"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/01"
msgid ""
"Oh, crap. Here we are, blessed with the beautiful colours of fall, the first "
"snowfall of the year, but a god damn hill full of Krauts suddenly stands in "
"our way."
msgstr ""
"Oh, mierda. Aquí estamos, bendecidos con los hermosos colores del otoño, la "
"primera nevada del año, en una maldita colina llena de alemanes que se "
"interpone en nuestro camino."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/02"
msgid ""
"We're gonna take Hill 400, Luitenant. My boys will test the German defences "
"and find our way in on the weakest spot."
msgstr ""
"Vamos a tomar la colina 400, Lugarteniente. Mis muchachos pondrán a prueba "
"las defensas alemanas y avanzaremos por el punto más débil."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/03"
msgid ""
"Knock it off! Those M12s are here to blow the hell out of the Germans. "
"Alright Soldiers, scout hill 400 and give us some coordinates for "
"bombardment."
msgstr ""
"¡Ya basta! Esos M12 están aquí para mandar a los alemanes al infierno. Está "
"bien, soldados, exploren la colina 400 y facilitarnos las coordenadas para "
"el bombardeo."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/04"
msgid ""
"Alright. Rangers!! I want that hill taken by nightfall, let's go! "
"Reinforcements and artillery are at your disposal. Rangers lead the way!"
msgstr ""
"Muy bien. ¡Rangers! Quiero esa colina tomada para el anochecer, ¡vamos! Los "
"refuerzos y la artillería están a vuestra disposición. ¡Los Rangers lideran "
"el camino!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/05"
msgid ""
"The Boches have some flak guns by the farm complex, threatening our "
"aircraft. If you can take them out, our boys will be able to rain hellfire "
"from the sky."
msgstr ""
"Los Boches tienen algunos cañones antiaéreos junto a la granja, amenazando a "
"nuestros aviones. Si puedes acabar con ellos, nuestros chicos podrán "
"descargar el fuego del infierno desde el cielo."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/06"
msgid ""
"Well done boys! That'll teach em! The Hill is ours. Jusging by the way they "
"fought for it, I don't think they'll be OK with giving it back that easily. "
"I want you to prepare for an imminent counterattack."
msgstr ""
"¡Bien hecho, chicos! ¡Eso les enseñará! La colina es nuestra. Juzgando por "
"la forma en que lucharon por ella, no creo que se retiren tan fácilmente. "
"Prepárense para un contraataque inminente."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/07"
msgid ""
"As you dwell into the forest, watch out for enemy foxholes everywhere. You "
"could be leaving enemy pockets behind you. These Germans, they know how to "
"camouflage their positions. Fan out and comb the entire area slowly."
msgstr ""
"Mientras avancen a través del bosque, tengan mucho cuidado con las "
"trincheras enemigas, están por todas partes. Si no se dan cuenta, podrían "
"dejar puñados de agujeros enemigos a sus espaldas. Esos alemanes saben bien "
"como camuflar sus posiciones. Desplegad las tropas y peinad toda la zona "
"lentamente."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/08"
msgid "Attention! Enemy counterattack! Hold them back!"
msgstr "¡Atención! ¡Contraataque enemigo! ¡Reténganlos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/09"
msgid ""
"They're fleeing! I don't trust them one bit, they'll come in later with more "
"friends. Keep Peppering those Krauts into mince meat!"
msgstr ""
"¡Están huyendo! No me fío ni una pizca de ellos, vendrán más tarde con sus "
"amigos. ¡Seguid haciendo picadillo a esos alemanes!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/10"
msgid "Alright, we gave them a run for their moneys again!"
msgstr "¡Muy bien, les hemos vuelto a dar una paliza!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/11"
msgid ""
"Well, we're not out of the woods just yet, quite literally. These documents "
"show the Fritzes think very highly of this hill. They're going to "
"counterattack us for sure. We need to build and dig in."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, aún no hemos salido del bosque, literalmente hablando. Estos "
"documentos muestran que los alemanes valoran mucho esta colina. Seguramente "
"contraatacarán. Necesitamos construir y cavar trincheras."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/12"
msgid ""
"The Engineers have arrived. It's time to build fortifications and lay mines "
"in the opposite direction. I want you to make these Krauts suffer as much as "
"we did to take this damn thing. "
msgstr ""
"Los Ingenieros han llegado. Es hora de construir fortificaciones y colocar "
"minas en la dirección opuesta. Quiero que hagan sufrir a estos alemanes "
"tanto como sufrimos nosotros para tomar esta maldita colina. "

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/13"
msgid ""
"We have very little time to build defences, so lay down mines on the most "
"obvious spots and don't get caught out of your foxholes when the Krauts show "
"up!"
msgstr ""
"Tenemos muy poco tiempo para construir defensas, así que colocad las minas "
"en los puntos más evidentes y ¡no os quedéis fuera de las trincheras cuando "
"aparezcan los alemanes!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/14"
msgid "Artillery barrage!!!"
msgstr "¡¡¡Bombardeo de artillería!!!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/15"
msgid "They've also brought mortars, watch out!"
msgstr "También han traído morteros, ¡cuidado!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/16"
msgid ""
"We've also received reports that the 6th Fallschirmjäger Regiment is in the "
"fight. German paratroopers, their very best! Watch out for those tough "
"cookies and send them straight to hell!"
msgstr ""
"También hemos recibido informes de que el 6º Regimiento Fallschirmjäger está "
"en la lucha. ¡Paracaidistas alemanes, lo mejor de lo mejor! ¡Tened cuidado "
"con esos tipos y mandadlos directamente al infierno!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/17"
msgid ""
"The weather has significantly worsened, so we can forget about air support..."
msgstr ""
"El tiempo ha empeorado significativamente, así que podemos olvidarnos del "
"apoyo aéreo..."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/18"
msgid "Shit! They brought mobile field guns!"
msgstr "¡Mierda! ¡Han traído artillería móvil!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/airstrike1"
msgid "P47 inbound, watch out for our bird!"
msgstr "¡P47 en camino, cuidado con nuestro pájaro!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/airstrike2"
msgid ""
"Alright boys, peace through superior firepower! Let's bomb the hell out of "
"the nazis!"
msgstr ""
"¡Muy bien chicos, consiguiendo la paz mediante un poder de fuego superior! "
"¡Bombardeemos a los nazis!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/airstrike3"
msgid "Airstrike underway, angels on our shoulders!"
msgstr "¡Ataque aéreo en marcha, nuestros ángeles nos protegen!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/flak1"
msgid "Flak gun down! Flak gun down! "
msgstr "¡Antiaéreo derribado! ¡Antiaéreo derribado! "

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/flak2"
msgid "Flak gun disabled, good job guys!"
msgstr "Antiaéreo destruido, ¡buen trabajo chicos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator/flak3"
msgid "Enemy triple-A down!"
msgstr "¡Antiaéreo abatido!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator2/01"
msgid "You hate to see it... What happens now, Sir?"
msgstr "Es difícil de afrontar... ¿Qué hacemos ahora, señor?"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator2/02"
msgid ""
"We could just go around it, Sir... For cryin' out loud, it's starting to "
"snow. What a beautiful day."
msgstr ""
"Podríamos rodearlo, señor... Por Dios, está empezando a nevar. Qué hermoso "
"día."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator2/03"
msgid ""
"Well guys, it's time for us to catch some rays, you know? 5th Armoured "
"division need us back at Bergstein. Pleasure to have slayed some nazis with "
"y'all today."
msgstr ""
"Bueno chicos, es hora de que tomemos un poco el sol, ¿no? La 5ª División "
"Blindada nos necesita de vuelta en Bergstein. Ha sido un placer matar nazis "
"con ustedes."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/narrator2/unable"
msgid "Target out of our range, you're gonna have to give us new coordinates."
msgstr "Objetivo fuera de alcance, tendrás que darnos nuevas coordenadas."

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/outro_completed"
msgid ""
"Excellent work soldiers! This victory shows the tenacity of the US Rangers, "
"keeping calm in the face of overwhelming odds. This hill seemed impregnable "
"at first sight, but you took it anyway. People will remember this battle for "
"a long time. You certainly made your mark as a commander today!"
msgstr ""
"¡Excelente trabajo soldados! Esta victoria demuestra la fortaleza de los "
"Rangers estadounidenses, manteniendo la calma frente a situaciones "
"imposibles. Esta colina parecía inexpugnable a primera vista, pero la "
"tomaron de todos modos. La gente recordará esta batalla durante mucho "
"tiempo. ¡Hoy has dejado evidencia de tu destreza como comandante!"

msgctxt "mission/single/04-usa/1944_12_hill400/outro_failed"
msgid ""
"This turned into a bad day somehow. If we fail to take this hill, our sole "
"advantage for the next battle is lost. This can’t be happening to the 2nd "
"Rangers, you must try again!"
msgstr ""
"Hoy no está siendo un gran día. Si fallamos en la toma de esta colina, "
"nuestra única ventaja para la próxima batalla está perdida. Esto no le puede "
"pasar a la 2da de Rangers, ¡deben intentarlo de nuevo!"

